EponE XV

‘YOU remember the night, Neaera, when you swore eterna! love to me. It is unhappy for you that 1 am not as light-minded as you. Your beauty will not tempt me back to you again. And for you, sir, my successful rival, be you ever so rich and wise and beautiful, you will be deserted as I have been, and 1 shall laugh at you yet.’
